# Game design context

Read `docs/GAME_DESIGN.md` before making gameplay or balance changes.

- **Active game:** 5×5 card-chain combat (`src/game/cardGame/`) played across a branching run map. Not tower defense.
- **Entry point:** `App.tsx` (run controller) → `RunMapOverlay` / `GameHud` / `RunEndOverlay` + `scenes/Game.ts` + `CardGameSession`.
- **Run flow:** map (pick node) → battle → win/lose. Scene starts/ends fights via `START_BATTLE` / `BATTLE_WON` / `BATTLE_LOST` events; HP carries over. See `src/game/run/runMap.ts`.
- **Determinism:** runs are seed-based. Use the seeded RNG in `src/game/random/rng.ts` (`random`/`randomInt`/`pickRandom`/`shuffleInPlace`) — never `Math.random()` in gameplay code.
- **Removed:** All TD code (towers, waves, fusion, races, targeting modes). Do not recreate or reference it.
- **Design goals:** Higher stakes (gauntlet, carry-over HP, scarce rerolls), deeper tactics (enemy counters, column pressure, telegraphed thresholds).
- **When changing systems:** Update `docs/GAME_DESIGN.md` changelog and roadmap checkboxes.
